---
source: crates/auspex/tests/contract.rs
expression: out
---
aus ls
  # every rule in the tree
  => exit 0: 4 rule(s)
aus ls csa
  # a scope that is a real node
  => exit 0: 3 rule(s)
aus ls nosuch
  # a scope naming no node
  => exit 4: no node with code "nosuch"
aus run
  # rule execution is not built yet
  => exit 1: `aus run` is not implemented yet — rule execution is the propose protocol's (§9.3), and `ls` is what reads the tree today
aus plan
  # nor is planning
  => exit 1: `aus plan` is not implemented yet — rule execution is the propose protocol's (§9.3), and `ls` is what reads the tree today
aus run (PANTHEON_RULE=1)
  # a rule may not re-enter the engine
  => exit 6: `run` re-enters the engine and PANTHEON_RULE=1 refuses it: a rule reads the tree through the core CLIs, never by calling `aus` — an `aus plan` inside a rule would re-evaluate that rule without bound (§9.3)
aus ls (PANTHEON_RULE=1)
  # but it may read
  => exit 0: 4 rule(s)
